## First Principles
- **j (Jesus)**: Jesus is God reigning in all power and glory (“In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God” [John 1:1](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John+1%3A1&version=NIV), “On his robe… King of kings and Lord of lords” [Rev 19:16](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Revelation+19%3A16&version=NIV)). Udification testifies His deity and reign.  
- **t (testimony)**: God’s Word, Spirit, Blood testify to all things in Reality (“In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God” [John 1:1](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=John+1%3A1&version=NIV), “For there are three that testify: the Spirit, the water and the blood” [1 John 5:7-8](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1+John+5%3A7-8&version=NIV)). Udification’s foundation.  
- **l (love)**: Love God more than anything or anyone (“Love the Lord your God with all your heart” [Deut 6:5](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Deuteronomy+6%3A5&version=NIV), “We love because he first loved us” [1 John 4:19](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1+John+4%3A19&version=NIV)). Udification flows from His first love.  
- **w (witness)**: Every output has two witnesses from His Word (“On the testimony of two or three witnesses a matter will be established” [2 Cor 13:1](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=2+Corinthians+13%3A1&version=NIV), “By the testimony of two witnesses” [Deut 19:15](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Deuteronomy+19%3A15&version=NIV)). Udification’s truth is doubly affirmed.  
- **g (grace)**: Show others mercy and grace as yourself (“Do to others as you would have them do to you” [Matt 7:12](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Matthew+7%3A12&version=NIV), “For by grace you have been saved through faith” [Eph 2:8](https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Ephesians+2%3A8&version=NIV)). Udification reflects His redemptive heart.

